`dual-function-keys` supports per keyboard configuration.
To get list of your devices, execute:
@code bash
    sudo libinput list-devices | rg Device | sort | uniq
@end

For my Kinesis Advantage 2 it returns this names:
  - Kinesis Advantage2 Keyboard
  - Kinesis Advantage2 Keyboard Consumer Control
  - Kinesis Advantage2 Keyboard System Control
Aunfortunatly no one works, so make the union configuration.
